++Watch me pull a wabbit outta my hat.++<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ushaethius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaethius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 6:59:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> Yip, 59 Chanter with Forlorn Deeds... I'd imagine a Ranger could provide after battle healing as well. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
With no slow, see how well Druids can keep up with the mob dmg output heh.<br>
<br>
Anyway, grats on PoF. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Shae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucaliopy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caliopy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 7:31:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> This reminds me of a time when I was 49 and lfg in Lguk.  I received a tell from someone saying. &quot;Bah who needs clerics?  we have a druid who is healing us and also snaring.  Clerics have been replaced permanently.&quot;  I can snare, too with my Regent symbol of Innoruuk casting clinging darkness, but I ignored his tell and continued lfg.  A few minutes later I get another tell from that same person asking if I can go to lord and rez their group.  I said have your druid rez you and gated out. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19612 
 Caliopy>Caliopy</a> 
<BR>58 Templar<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kindly Poster</span><br>  Posts: 499<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 8:17:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> Ya, we had a camp-out cleric.  My post was somewhat tongue-in-cheek.  And we worked VERY hard to kite mobs and only bring 1-2 to camp.  It takes a lot longer that way, but it works if you're patient.<br>
<br>
But still, you CAN do things when you're apparantly under-forced.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucaliopy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caliopy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 8:29:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> I understand what you were saying, Wolfypaw, just reminded me of what happened in Lguk that day, but you're right...we have gone full circle.  Remember when you were lvl 8 and you formed groups with any class that showed up?  You didn't ask for a cleric, enchanter, shammy, wizzie, warrior, or whatever, and you did just fine.  As we get higher in lvl, we have learned ways to compensate for not having a particular class in our groups.  Other classes can provide some sort of replacement, maybe not as well as the replaced class, but well enough to get the job done. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19612 
 Caliopy>Caliopy</a> 
<BR>58 Templar<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warmly Poster</span><br>  Posts: 504<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 8:52:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> What was fun about this was that we really didn't think we could do it.  A few people told me in tells it was going to be a blowout.  I sent back -- if everyone stays in camp except the pullers, and the pullers stay well clear of camp unless they know they only have 1-2, then only the pullers die.<br>
<br>
And that's how it worked.  Destyni died a couple of times -- there were some dispelling mobs in the temple, there goes SOW.  Wolfy died a few times.<br>
<br>
We left when we lost the other druid.  There were 6 or 7 mobs left in the temple.  We probably good have pulled it okay -- someone other than Wolfy would have had to kite, no biggie.  But everyone was tired, and it was time to go to bed.<br>
<br>
I guess I'm just pleased when I manage to accomplish something without being a zerg.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ushaethius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaethius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 8:57:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> I've been saying this all along. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Back in the summer of 99 when I had a Ranger. A typical group of ours for Live Tower in Lguk consisted of:<br>
<br>
43 Cleric<br>
43 Monk<br>
43 Enchanter<br>
42 Ranger<br>
41 Ranger<br>
Occassionaly misc Druid<br>
<br>
Our 'Chanter was good enough that our Cleric either spent her whole time sitting, or nuking. Hardly ever healing, and the healing she was doing could have been easily accomplished after the battle. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  *note* This wasn't a bad Cleric, she was just bored... in circumstances where healing was greatly needed, she was one of the best. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
With good enough crowd control (atleast until you hit some 55+ mobs) you shouldn't need all that much healing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
The whole reason for Shae was for perma rez's for my Monk and my friends. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ok, I fullfilled my months quote of Emoticons. heh<br>
<br>
Shae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulaelia666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laelia666</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#778899>(11/15/01 9:19:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who Needs Clerics</span><hr size=1> I like this post....in all but the heaviest trains druids are as good as clerics at healing.  When I was working on my epic, we had one druid healing 2 groups for Vessel Drozlin in Cabilis...the cleric went down after the first c-heal on the monk taunted Vessel onto him.  The monk went down shortly after.   We finished the fight bruised and battered with one monk, 2 paladins, and my pet taking most of the heat from Vessel....but it was done.<br>
<br>
The defining cleric skill in my mind is the ability to cast symbols.  I have about 1000 HP with self buffs.  Over 2200 with symbol of marzin and heroic bond.  With a meager 1000 HP against a couple hasted krup knights and shamen, most enchanters wont last long.  Ditto for Amy temple pulls, which can include harm touches and lots of mez resists.<br>
<br>
No offense to druids...I don't usually go into battle without a decent cleric around <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17550">Laelia Jadebreaker</a><BR>
